      "writtenOn": "2026-03-17T12:27:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m biased of course, but I quite like github.com/rogpeppe/retry as an API for retries, which not only keeps the retry strategy nicely separate from the actual code logic (and uses well tested logic for that), but also makes it trivial to stop immediately when the context is cancelled.\n\nIt might look something like this (untested):\n\n```\n\nvar connectStrategy \u003d retry.Strategy{\n\tDelay:    250 * time.Millisecond,\n\tMaxDelay: 15 * time.Second,\n}\n\n// connect repeatedly attempts to connect to the external\n// validator. Whenever the connection closes, or fails to connect, the\n// go-routine sleeps, following a randomised binary exponential\n// backoff schedule. The go-routine will only exit if the context\n// supplied to [connect] errors.\nfunc (c *conn) connect() {\n\tprofile :\u003d c.profile\n\tserverUrl :\u003d profile.ServerURL\n\tctx :\u003d c.ctx\n\n\titer :\u003d connectStrategy.Start()\n\tfor {\n\t\tvar dialOpts *websocket.DialOptions\n\n\t\tif profile.Token !\u003d \"\" {\n\t\t\tdialOpts \u003d \u0026websocket.DialOptions{\n\t\t\t\tHTTPHeader: http.Header{\n\t\t\t\t\t\"Authorization\": {\"Bearer \" + profile.Token},\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tconn, resp, err :\u003d websocket.Dial(ctx, serverUrl+wsPath, dialOpts)\n\t\tif err !\u003d nil {\n\t\t\tif resp \u003d\u003d nil {\n\t\t\t\tc.debugLogf(\"extValidator: error when dialing %s: %v\", serverUrl, err)\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\tc.debugLogf(\"extValidator: error when dialing %s: %v, http status: %v\", serverUrl, err, resp.StatusCode)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif !iter.Next(ctx.Done()) {\n\t\t\t\t// This can only happen if the context is cancelled.\n\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tc.debugLogf(\"extValidator: connected to %s\", serverUrl)\n\t\tc.lock.Lock()\n\t\tc.conn \u003d conn\n\t\tc.lock.Unlock()\n\n\t\tc.receive(conn)\n\n\t\tc.lock.Lock()\n\t\tc.conn \u003d nil\n\t\tc.lock.Unlock()\n\t\titer.Reset(\u0026connectStrategy, nil)\n\t}\n}\n```",
      "revId": "fd2f3afd0ac993d8ec1cab2cade91b6ac2c43769",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
